obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43130)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43130&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Panjab District Boards Act, 1883.`
  line
  line `Extent.--(2) It shall extend only to the territories for the time being administered by`
  line `the Lieutenant-Governor of the Panjab; and`
  line
  line `Commencement.--(3) It shall come into force in each district on such date as the Local`
  line `Government, by notification, directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43131)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Repeal of Act V of 1878.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43131&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `From the date on which this Act comes into force in any district, the`
  line `Panjab Local Rates Act, 1878 (V of 1878), shall be repealed throughout that district. But all rates`
  line `imposed, sums credited to the Local Government, and notifications published under that Act, shall, so far`
  line `as may be, be deemed to have been respectively spectively imposed, credited and published under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43132)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43132&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `(1) "Land" means land assessed to the land-revenue, and includes land whereof the land-revenue has`
  line `been wholly, or in part, released, compounded for, redeemed or assigned.`
  line
  line `(2) "Land-revenue" includes trini or grazing-dues levied for grazing on Government lands under`
  line `section 48 of the Panjab Laws Act, 1872 (IV of 1872).`
  line
  line `(3) "Landholder" means any person responsible for the payment of the land-revenue, if any,`
  line `assessed on land. It also includes the proprietor of land the land-revenue of which has been wholly, or in`
  line `part, released, compounded for, redeemed or assigned.`
  line
  line `(4) "Annual value" means--`
  line
  line `(a) double the land-revenue for the time being assessed on any land, whether the assessment is`
  line `leviable or not ; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the land-revenue has been permanently assessed, or has been wholly or in part compounded for or redeemed, double the amount which, but for such permanent assessment,`
  line `composition or redemption, would have been leviable; or`
  line
  line `(c) where no land-revenue has been assessed, double the amount which would have been`
  line `assessed if the average village-rate had been applied:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in any tract in which, under the settlement for the time being in force, the`
  line `improvement of the land due to canal irrigation has been excluded from account in assessing the`
  line `land-revenue, and a rate has been imposed in respect of such improvement, that rate shall be`
  line `added to the land-revenue for the purpose of computing the annual value.`
  line
  line `(5) "Financial year" means the year commencing on the first day of April.`
  line
  line `(6) "Prescribed day "means such day as the Local Government may, from time to time, prescribe.`
  line
  line `^1[(6A) "Punjab" means the territories which, immediately before the Ist November, 1956, were`
  line `comprised in the State with the same name];`
  line
  line `(7) "Notification" means a notification published in the official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(8) "Notified" means notified in the official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(9) "Deputy Commissioner" means the Deputy Commissioner of a district, and includes any`
  line `officer specially appointed by the Local Government to perform the functions of a Deputy`
  line `Commissioner under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43133)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Powers exercisable from time to time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43133&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `All powers conferred by this Act may be exercised from`
  line `time to time as occasion requires.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43134)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `The local rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43134&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) All land shall be subject to the payment The local of a rate, to be called the`
  line `local rate, not exceeding one rate annual for every rupee of its annual value.`
  line
  line `(2) The proportion which the local rate shall bear to the annual value of land shall, except as provided`
  line `in sub-section (3), be fixed for each district by the Local Government by notification.`
  line
  line `(3) The Local Government may, by notification, delegate to the district board, subject to such`
  line `restrictions or conditions as it thinks fit, its powers under sub-section (2), and may, by`
  line `notification, cancel or vary any such notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43135)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Road, school and post cesses to merge in the rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43135&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `From such date as may be notified in`
  line `respect of each district by the Local Government, all authorized rates and cesses for the`
  line `maintenance of roads, schools and the district-post shall merge in and become part of the local rate,`
  line `and no rate or cess other than the local rate shall be thereafter leviable for those purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (43136)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Liability for local rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43136&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The landholder shall be liable for the local rate subject to the following`
  line `provisos, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) where the landholder pays the land-revenue in kind to any assignee of revenue or any villageheadman, the assignee of revenue or village-headman shall be liable for the payment of the local rate instead of the landholder, and no demand shall be made by any such assignee or village-headman on the`
  line `landholder in respect of the payment of the rate; and`
  line
  line `(2) where the Government has, under any lease current at the time when this Act comes into force,`
  line `paid the Focal rate on trini, it shall continue to pay the rate during the currency of the lease.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (43137)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to recover a share of the rate from occupancy-tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43137&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `When a local rate is payable`
  line `by a landholder in respect of lands held by a tenant with a right of occupancy holding at a favourable`
  line `rent, the landholder may realize from the tenant a share of the rate, bearing the same proportion to the`
  line `whole rate as the excess of the annual value over the rent paid by the tenant bears to half the annual`
  line value.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (43138)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Appropriation of proceeds of local rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43138&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Four-fifths of the net proceeds of the local rate levied`
  line `in each district, after deducting the expenses of collection, shall, except as provided in section 68, be`
  line `allotted to the district board established for that district under this Act.`
  line
  line `The remaining one-fifth shall be carried to the credit of the Local Government, and may--`
  line
  line `(a) be allotted by that Government to any district board established under this Act ; or`
  line
  line `(b) be applied by that Government to provide in the territories to which this Act extends, or any`
  line `part thereof, for any of the matters on which district boards may expend the funds at their disposal`
  line `under this Act :`
  line
  line `Provided that the Local Government may direct that the whole or any portion of the net proceeds of`
  line `the local rate levied within the limits of any municipality or military cantonment,. after deducting the expenses collection, shall be carried to the credit of the municipal fund, or made available for the purpose of public`
  line `improvement in the cantonment or for carrying out therein any rules made under section 25 of the Cantonments`
  line `Act, 1880 (III of 11880), as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (43140)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Establishment of district and local boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43140&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government shall, by`
  line `notification establish a district board for each district.`
  line
  line `(2) The Local Government may, by notification, establish a local board or local boards within`
  line `the limits of any district, and may cancel or vary any such notification.`
  line
  line `(3) A district board shall have authority throughout the district for which it is established, and a local`
  line `board shall have authority throughout such portion of the district in which it is established, as the Local`
  line `Government may, by notification, direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that a board shall not have authority over any portion of a district which is for the time`
  line `being included in a military cantonment or a municipality.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (43141)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Number and appointment or election of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43141&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) A district board or local board shall`
  line `consist of such number of members, not less than six, as the Local Government may fix in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The members may be appointed by the Local Government either by name or by official`
  line `designation, or may be elected in accordance with rules made by the Local Government under this Act, or`
  line `some may be appointed and some elected, as the Local Government directs:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) when the Local Government has directed that all or any proportion of the members shall`
  line `be elected, it shall not thereafter direct that they shall be appointed, unless a majority of the`
  line `electors declare that they so desire, ^1***;`
  line
  line `(b) ^2*** unless salaried officers of the Government are elected, not less than two-thirds of the`
  line `members of every board shall be persons other than salaried officers of the Government; and`
  line
  line `(c) not less than one-half of the members of the board shall be landholders in the district.`
  line
  line `(3) When, under a direction issued under sub-section (2), any places on a board are required to be`
  line `filled by election, and a sufficient number of members is not elected, the Local Government may fill those`
  line `places by appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or the Governor General in Council, for some reason affecting the public interests, sanctions the`
  line `direction," omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule`
  line
  line `2. The words "except with the approval of the Governor General in Council or" omitted by s. 2 and the First`
  line `Schedule, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (43142)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Term of office of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43142&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) A member of a district board or local board, when appointed`
  line `by virtue of an office, shall, unless and until the Local Government otherwise directs, continue to b e`
  line `a member of the board while he continues to hold that office.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of all other elected and appointed members respectively of a district`
  line `board or local board shall be fixed by the Local Government by rules made under this Act, and`
  line `may be so fixed as to provide for the retirement of members by rotation, but shall not exceed three`
  line years.
  line
  line `(3) An outgoing member shall, if otherwise qualified, be again eligible for election or appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (43143)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Resignation of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43143&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A member of a local board or of a district board may resign by`
  line `notifying in writing his intention to do so to ^1[Commissioner]; and, on the acceptance by ^1[Commissioner]`
  line `of such resignation, the member shall be deemed to have vacated his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (43144)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Powers of the Local Government as to removal of mothers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43144&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Local Government may`
  line `remove any member of a district board or local board--`
  line
  line `(a) if he refuses to act, or becomes incapable of acting, or is declared insolvent, or is`
  line `convicted of any such offence, or subjected by a Criminal Court to any such order, as implies, in the opinion of the Local Government, a defect of character which unfits him to be a`
  line `member ;`
  line
  line `(b) if he has been declared by notification to be disqualified for employment in the`
  line `public service;`
  line
  line `(c) if he, being a member of a local board, without an excuse sufficient in the opinion of`
  line `the Local Government, neglects for more than three consecutive months to be present at the`
  line `meetings of that board, or, being a member of the district board, without such sufficient`
  line `excuse, neglects for more than six consecutive months to be present at the meetings of that`
  line board;
  line
  line `(d) if his continuance in office is, in the opinion of the Local Government, dangerous to the`
  line `public peace or order ; or,`
  line
  line `(e) when he is a salaried officer of the Government, if his continuance in office is; in the opinion`
  line `of the Local Government, unnecessary or undesirable.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (43145)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Filling of casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43145&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the place of an elected member of a local board or`
  line `district board becomes vacant by the resignation or removal of the member or by his death, a new`
  line `member shall be chosen in accordance with 'the rules made by the Local Government under this Act to`
  line `fill the place :`
  line
  line `Provided that the Local Government may direct in any such case that the vacancy shall be left`
  line unfilled.
  line
  line `(2) When the place of a member of a local board or district board appointed by name becomes`
  line `vacant as aforesaid, the Local Government may, if it thinks fit, appoint a new member to fill the`
  line place.
  line
  line `(3) A person chosen or appointed under this section to fill a casual vacancy shall hold office until`
  line `the person whose place he fills would regularly have gone out of office, and shall then go out of`
  line `office, but shall be again eligible for election or appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (43146)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Incorporation of district boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43146&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Every district board shall be a body corporate by the`
  line `name of the district board of its district, and shall have perpetual succession and a common seal,`
  line `with power to acquire and hold property, both moveable and immoveable, and, subject to any rules`
  line `made by the Local Government under this Act, to transfer any such property held by it, and to`
  line `contract and do all other things necessary for the purposes of its constitution, and may sue and be`
  line `sued in its corporate name.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (43147)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Time for district and local boards coming into existence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43147&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The several district boards and`
  line `local boards constituted under this Act shall come into existence at such time as the Local`
  line `Government may, by notification, fix in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (43148)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Chairman.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43148&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) A member of every district board or local board shall be elected or`
  line `appointed to be chairman of the board, and shall hold office for such term, not exceeding three years,`
  line `as the Local Government may, by a rule made under this Act, fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The Local Government shall determine, as regards each board or as regards any class of`
  line `boards, whether the chairman shall be a person appointed by virtue of his office or by name or be`
  line elected.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (43149)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Vice-chairman.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43149&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A district board or local board may elect one of its members to be vicechairman.`
  line
  line `(2) A vice-chairman so elected shall hold office for such term as the board may, by rule, fix.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (43151)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Duties of district board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43151&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following matters shall, subject to such exceptions and.`
  line `conditions as the Local Government may make and impose, be under the control and. administration of`
  line `each district board within the area subject to its authority :--`
  line
  line `(a) the management of all property vested in the district board ;`
  line
  line `(b) the construction, repair and maintenance of public roads and other means of communication;`
  line
  line `(c) the establishment, management, maintenance and visiting of public hospitals,`
  line `dispensaries, sarais and schools, and the construction and repair of all buildings connected with`
  line `these institutions;`
  line
  line `(d) the training of teachers and the establishment of scholarships ;`
  line
  line `(e) the supply, storage and preservation from pollution of water for drinking, cooking and bathing`
  line `purposes ; and.`
  line
  line `(f) the planting and preservation of trees.`
  line
  line `(2) The Local Government may direct that any of the following. matters shall, subject to such`
  line `exceptions and conditions as it may make and impose, be under the control and administration of`
  line `a district board Within the area subject to its authority :--`
  line
  line `(g) the management of any property vested in Her Majesty ;`
  line
  line `(h) the establishment, maintenance, visiting and management of markets, rest-houses, encampinggrounds and other public institutions, and the construction and repair or all buildings connected with`
  line `these institutions ;`
  line
  line `(i) the construction and repair of embankments, and the supply, storage and control of water for`
  line `agricultural purposes ;`
  line
  line `(j) the preservation and reclamation of soil, and the drainage and reclamation of swamps ;`
  line
  line `(k) the construction, repair and maintenance of famine preventive works, and the establishment and maintenance of such relief-works, relief-houses and other measures in time of famine`
  line `or scarcity as may be entrusted to the charge of the board by the Local Government ;`
  line
  line `(l) the registration of births, marriages and deaths ;`
  line
  line `(m) fairs and agricultural shows and industrial exhibitions ;`
  line
  line `(n) the establishment and management of pounds, including, where the Cattle-trespass Act`
  line `1871 (1 of 1871), is in force, such functions of the Local Government and the Magistrate of`
  line `the district under that Act as may be transferred to the board by the Local Government ;`
  line
  line `(o) the management of such public ferries as may be entrusted to the charge of the board`
  line `under section 7A of the Northern India Ferries Act, 1878, as amended by this Act`
  line
  line `(p) any other local works or measures likely to promote the health, comfort, convenience and`
  line `interests of the public or the agricultural or industrial prosperity of the country; and`
  line
  line `(q) any other matters which the Local Govern-went may declare to be fit and proper`
  line `matters to be taken under the control and administration of the board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Local Government may cancel or modify any direction given by it under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) A district board shall, so far as the funds at its disposal permit, make due provision for all matters`
  line `placed under its control or administration by or under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (43153)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Duties of local board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43153&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government, or, subject to the control of the Local`
  line `Government, a district board, may direct that, within the area subject to the authority of a local board, any matter placed under the control and administration of the district board by or under`
  line `section 20 shall be transferred to the control and administration of the local board.`
  line
  line `(2) A local board, as the agent of, and subject to the control of, the district board, shall, so far as the`
  line `funds at its disposal permit, make due provision for all matters transferred to its control and administration under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the duty of the district board to enforce the responsibility imposed on a local board by`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (43154)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Limits on expenditure of local board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43154&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Except as otherwise provided by this Act, a local board`
  line `shall not incur expenses or undertake liabilities expenditure to any amount exceeding the limit imposed`
  line `by of local board the district board of its district.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (43155)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power for district board to provide for performance of duty in default of local board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43155&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `a local board makes default in the performance of any duty imposed on it by or under this Act, the district`
  line `board may, by order in writing, fix a period of board of its district.`
  line
  line `(2) If the duty is not performed within that period, the district board may appoint some person`
  line `to perform it, and may provide for the expenses of, and incidental to, its performance out of the funds`
  line `appropriated to or for the purposes of the local board.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (43157)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Joint committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43157&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `A district board may concur with any other district board, or with any`
  line `municipal committee or with any cantonment authority, or with more than one such board, committee or`
  line `authority, in appointing, out of their respective bodies, a joint committee for any purpose in which they`
  line `are jointly interested, and for delegating to any such joint committee any power which might be exercised`
  line `by either or nay of the boards, committees or authorities concerned, and in framing or modifying`
  line `regulations as to the proceedings of any such joint committee, and as to the conduct of correspondence`
  line `relating to the purpose for which the joint committee is appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (43159)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Record and publication of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43159&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Minutes of the proceedings at each meeting of a district or local board shall be drawn up and recorded in a book to be kept for the`
  line `purpose, and shall be signed by the chairman of the meeting or of the next ensuing meeting, and`
  line `shall be published in such manner as the Local Government may, from time to time, direct, and`
  line `shall, at all reasonable times and without charge, be open to the inspection of any inhabitant of`
  line `the district who pays any rate or tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every resolution passed by a local board at a meeting shall, within three days`
  line `from the date of the meeting, be forwarded to the district board and to the Deputy Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every resolution passed by a district board at a meeting shall, within three days from`
  line `the date of the meeting, be forwarded to the Deputy Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (43160)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to make rules as to business and affairs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43160&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every district board, and every local`
  line `board with the sanction of the district board, may make rules as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the time and place of its meetings and the manner in which notice of meetings shall be`
  line `given ;`
  line
  line `(b) the conduct of proceedings at meetings and the adjournment of meetings;`
  line
  line `(c) the custody of the common seal and the purposes for which it shall be used ;`
  line
  line `(d) the division of duties amongst its members ;`
  line
  line `(e) the powers to be exercised by sub-committees or members to whom particular duties have`
  line `been assigned;`
  line
  line `(f) the persons by whom receipts shall be granted for money received under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) the duties, appointment, leave, suspension and removal of the officers and servants of the`
  line board;
  line
  line `(h) the term for which the vice-chairman shall hold office, and`
  line
  line `(i) other similar matters :`
  line
  line `Provided that every rule made under this section must be consistent with this Act and with any rules`
  line `made by the Local Government under this Act, and shall be published in such manner as the Local Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (43162)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Employment of officers and servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43162&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and to any`
  line `rules which may be made under this Act in servants this behalf, every district board may employ and`
  line `pay such officers and servants as may be necessary and proper for the efficient execution of its duties and`
  line `of the duties of the local boards acting under it :`
  line
  line `Provided that if, at any time, in the opinion of the Deputy Commissioner,--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of persons employed by a board under this section, or the remuneration`
  line `assigned by the board to those persons, or to any of them, is excessive, or`
  line
  line `(b) any such person is unfit for his employment, the board shall, on the requirement of the`
  line `Deputy Commissioner, reduce the number, or remuneration, of those persons, or, as the -case may be,`
  line `dismiss the unfit person.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner of the division, whose decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (43163)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Pensions of Government officials serving boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the Second Schedule, for "Government Civil Pension and Leave Codes".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43163&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a Government official, a`
  line `district board may--`
  line
  line `(1) if his services are wholly lent to it, contribute to his pension or gratuity and leave-allowances in`
  line `accordance with the rules of the ^1[Civil Service Regulations] for the time being in force ; and`
  line
  line `(2) if he devotes only a part of his time to the performance of duties in behalf of the board, contribute`
  line `to his pension or gratuity and leave-allowances in such proportion as may be determined by the`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (43164)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Pensions of servants of boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the Second Schedule, for "Government Civil Pension and Leave Codes".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43164&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `In the case of an officer or servant, not being a Government`
  line `official referred to in section 28, a district board may--`
  line
  line `(1) grant him leave-allowances and, if he is employed under the district committee when this Act`
  line `comes into force and not entitled to pension, or if his monthly pay is less than ten rupees, a gratuity ; and`
  line
  line `(2) if empowered in this behalf by the Local Government--`
  line
  line `(a) subscribe in his behalf for pension or gratuity and leave-allowances under the rules of the`
  line `Government Civil Pension and Leave Codes for the time being in force ; or`
  line
  line `(b) purchase for him from the Government or otherwise an annuity on his retirement :`
  line
  line `Provided that no pension, gratuity, leave-allowance or annuity shall exceed the sum to which, under`
  line `the ^1[Civil Service Regulations] for the time being in force, the servant would be entitled if the service`
  line `had been service under the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (43166)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Powers of taxation conferred on district boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for "Governor General in Council".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43166&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any general rules or special`
  line `orders which the ^1[Local Government] may make in this behalf, a district board may impose, in manner`
  line `prescribed by section 31, such taxes as may be approved by the Local Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such tax shall be imposed in respect of any property subject to the local rate.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (43167)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Procedure in imposing taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43167&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) A district board may resolve, at a meeting, convened and`
  line `constituted in such manner as the Local Government may prescribe, to propose the imposition of any`
  line `tax under section 30.`
  line
  line `(2) When a resolution has been passed under subsection (1), the board shall publish a notice defining`
  line `the class of persons or description of property proposed to be taxed, the amount or rate of the tax to be`
  line `imposed and the system of assessment to be adopted.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person likely to be directly affected by the proposed tax, and objecting to the same, may,`
  line `within thirty days from the publication of the notice, send his objection in writing to the board ; and the`
  line `board shall, at a meeting convened and constituted as aforesaid, take his objection into consideration.`
  line
  line `(4) If no objection is sent within the said period of thirty days, or if the objections received, having`
  line `been considered as aforesaid, are deemed insufficient, the board may submit its proposals to the Local`
  line `Government, with the objections (if any) which have been sent in and with its decision thereon.`
  line
  line `(5) The Local Government, on receiving proposals under sub-section (4), may sanction the same, or`
  line `refuse to sanction them, or return them to the board for further consideration.`
  line
  line `(6) When the proposals of a district board in respect of a tax have been sanctioned by the Local`
  line `Government, the board may, at a meeting convened and constituted as aforesaid, direct the imposition of`
  line `the tax in accordance with those proposals:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in giving such direction, the board shall fix a date not less than one month from the`
  line `date of the meeting on which the tax shall come into force.`
  line
  line `(7) Every direction under sub-section (6) shall be notified, and the notification shall be conclusive`
  line `evidence that the tax has been imposed in accordance with law.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (43168)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Reduction and abolition of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43168&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Local Government may, by notification, and the district`
  line `board may, with the sanction of the Local Government, by a resolution passed at a meeting convened and`
  line `constituted as the Local Government may prescribe, abolish or reduce any tax imposed under sections 30`
  line `and 31`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (43169)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Levy of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43169&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `With the previous sanction of the Local Government, or of such officer as the`
  line `Local Government may authorize in this behalf, a district board or local board may fix and levy schoolfees and fees for the use of, or benefits derived from, any of the works specified in section 20, clauses (c),`
  line `(e), (h), (i) and KB, and fees at fairs, agricultural shows and. industrial exhibitions held under its`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (43170)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Additional funds to be provided by the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43170&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `When the control and administration of`
  line `any matter is by or under this Act transferred to a district board, and at the time of the transfer the cost of`
  line `that control and administration is defrayed from provincial revenue, the Local Government shall, from`
  line `time to time, allot to the district board such funds, .or place at the disposal of the board such sources of`
  line `income, as may, in the opinion of the Local Government and of the board, be sufficient for maintaining`
  line `the control and administration of the said matter in the state of efficiency existing at the date of transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (43171)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `District fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43171&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `There Shall be formed for each district a fund, to be called the district fund, andthere shall lie placed to the credit thereof--`
  line
  line `(a) the balance (if any) of the allotments made for the district under section 7 of the Panjab Local`
  line `Bates Act, 1878 (V of 1887), and of the road and school ceases, which may be available for`
  line `expenditure in the district on the day on which the district board comes into existence;`
  line
  line `(b) all proceeds of rates allotted to the district board under section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) the proceeds of all taxes imposed in the district under sections 30 and 31;`
  line
  line `(d) the amount of all fees levied by the district board or by local boards in the district under`
  line `section 33;`
  line
  line `(e) all funds allotted to the district board and the income arising from 'all sources of income placed`
  line `at its disposal under section 34;`
  line
  line `(f) all rents and profits accruing from property vested in the district board or managed by the`
  line `district board or a local board in the district;`
  line
  line `(g) all sums contributed to the fund by Government or by any committee, board or private person;`
  line
  line `(h) all sums received by the district board or by a local board in the district in the discharge ,of`
  line `functions exercised by it under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(i) the proceeds of all sources of income which the Local Government may order to be placed at,`
  line `the disposal of the district board :`
  line
  line `Provided that the Meal Government may revoke any order made .under clause (i).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (43172)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Vesting, custody and investment of district fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43172&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The district fund shall be vested in the`
  line `district board, and the balance standing at the credit of the fund shall be kept in the Government treasury or`
  line `sub-treasury or in the bank to which the Government treasury business has been made over, unless the Local`
  line `Government in any cases otherwise permits.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such rules as the ^7[Local Government, subject to the control of the] Governor General`
  line `in Council may make in this behalf, the district board may, with the previous sanction of the Local`
  line `Government, invest any portion of the district fund in securities of the Government of India or such other`
  line `securities as the ^1[Local Government, subject to the control of the] Governor General in Council may`
  line `approve in this behalf, and vary such investments for others of the same nature, or dispose of them. The`
  line `income resulting from the securities, and the proceeds of the sale of the same, shall be credited to the`
  line `district fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (43173)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Application of district fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43173&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The district fund shall be charged with the payment of the`
  line `expenses of the district-post, the payment of the expenses of pauper lunatics sent to public asylums from`
  line `the area under the authority of the district board, the expenses incurred in auditing the accounts of the`
  line `district boards and local boards, and such portion of the cost of the Provincial Departments for education,`
  line `sanitation, vaccination, medical relief and public works as may be held by the Local Government to be`
  line `equitably debitable to the district board in return for services rendered to the board by those Departments.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the charges specified in sub-section (1), and to such rules as the Local Government may`
  line `make with respect to the priority to be given to the several duties of the board or otherwise, the district`
  line `fund shall be applicable to the payment, in whole or in part, of the charges and expenses incidental to the`
  line `matters specified in sections 20, 27, 28 and 29, and to the provision of grants-in-aid to educational and`
  line `medical institutions, within the area subject to the authority of the district board, and, with the sanction of`
  line `the Commissioner, outside that area when such application of the fund is for the benefit of the inhabitants`
  line `of that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (43174)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Works or undertakings benefiting several districts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43174&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `In the case of works or undertakings`
  line `which undertakings benefit more districts than one, when the district boards cannot agree, the`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioners of the division or divisions, or, when the districts are in different`
  line `divisions and the Commissioners cannot agree, the Local Government, may determine what proportion of`
  line `the expenses of the work or undertaking shall be borne by each of the district funds of the districts`
  line `benefited thereby ; and such proportion shall be payable out of the several district funds accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (43175)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Annual estimates of income and expenditure of district boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43175&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every district board shall`
  line `appoint a finance committee consisting of not less than three of its members.`
  line
  line `(2) Every district board shall, on or before a boards prescribed day in each year, hold a meeting at`
  line `which the finance committee shall submit to the board an estimate of the income and expenditure of the`
  line `board for the next financial year, in such form as the Local Government may, by a rule made under this`
  line `Act, prescribe.`
  line
  line `(3) The board shall consider the estimate, and may provisionally approve of it .with or without`
  line modification.
  line
  line `(4) The board shall, on or before a prescribed day, cause copies of the estimate, as provisionally`
  line `approved by it, to be sent to the Deputy Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(5) The Deputy Commissioner shall, on or before a, prescribed day, signify in writing to the board his`
  line `approval or disapproval of the estimate. When he disapproves of the estimate, he shall state the nature of his objection. The board shall then consider the matter, and either modify the estimate, so as to remove`
  line `the objection, or refer it through the Deputy Commissioner to the Commissioner of the division. If the`
  line `Commissioner concurs in the objection, he shall make such modification in the estimate as may, in his`
  line `judgment, be necessary to remove the objection in whole or in part. If he does not concur in the objection,`
  line `he shall pass the estimate, and his order shall be final and binding on the board.`
  line
  line `(6) When the Deputy Commissioner has signified his approval of an estimate, or the board has`
  line `modified an estimate so as to remove the Deputy Commissioner's objections, or when the Commissioner`
  line `has passed orders as provided in sub-section (5), no expenditure which is not provided for in the estimate`
  line `as approved or modified shall be incurred during the year to which the estimate relates without the`
  line `previous sanction of the Deputy Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(7) When the Deputy Commissioner is a member of the district board, the Commissioner and the`
  line `Local Government shall take the place of the Deputy Commissioner and the Commissioner respectively`
  line `for the purposes of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (43176)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Accounts of district boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43176&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Accounts of the receipts and expenditure of every district board`
  line `shall be made up periodically to such days and in such form as the Local Government prescribes, and`
  line `shall be examined and. audited as soon as may be after they are so made up by such persons as the Local`
  line `Government appoints in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (43177)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Estimates and accounts of local boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43177&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every local board shall submit annually to the`
  line `district board of its district, on or before such date as the district board may appoint in this behalf, a`
  line `statement of the requirements, and an estimate of the probable expenditure, of the local board for the`
  line `coming financial year, and shall submit, as often as the district board may require, accounts of its receipts`
  line `and expenditure.`
  line
  line `(2) The district board shall signify in. writing to the local board its approval or disapproval of an`
  line `estimate submitted under this section, and powers similar to those conferred on the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `and Commissioner by section 39, clauses, (5) and (6), shall be exercised, in regard to the estimate, by the`
  line `district board and the Deputy Commissioner, or (when the Deputy Commissioner is a member of the`
  line `district board) the Commissioner, respectively`
  line
  line `Provided that, during the currency of any financial year, the Deputy Commissioner may sanction`
  line `transfers of provision within the estimate finally' approved, when inconvenience or undue delay would be`
  line `caused by a previous reference to the district board.`
  line
  line `(3) The district board shall make arrangements, subject to the approval of the Deputy Commissioner,`
  line `for the examination and. audit of accounts submitted to it under this section, and may arrange for the`
  line `publication of such accounts.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (43178)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Inspection of estimates and accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43178&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Every district board shall cause a copy of every annual`
  line `estimate provisionally or finally approved under section 39, and of every account made up under section`
  line `40, to be kept at its office; and any person paying rates or taxes under this Act may, at all reasonable`
  line `times, inspect any such estimate or account without payment of any fee.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (43179)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Publication of abstract of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43179&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `A statement of the accounts of a district board for each`
  line `financial year, showing the income of the district fund under each head. of receipt, the charges for`
  line `establishment, the works undertaken, the sums expended on each work, and the balance, if any, of the`
  line `fund remaining unspent at the end of the year, shall be prepared by the board in such form as the Local`
  line `Government prescribes; and an abstract of the same shall be published in the English and Vernacular`
  line `official Gazettes, or in such other manner as the Local Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (43181)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Control of Commissioner and Deputy Commissioner over boards and joint committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43181&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Commissioner of the division, or the Deputy Commissioner of the district when he is not a member`
  line `of the district board, may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter on and inspect, or cause to be entered on and inspected, any immoveable property within`
  line `the limits of the division or district respectively occupied by any local board, district board or joint committee, or any work in progress within those limits under the direction of any such board or`
  line committee;
  line
  line `(b) by order in writing call for and inspect any document in the possession or under the control of`
  line `any such board or committee having authority within those limits;`
  line
  line `(c) by order in writing require any such board or committee to furnish such statements, accounts,`
  line `reports and copies of documents relating to the proceedings or duties of the board or committee, as he`
  line `may think fit to call for; and`
  line
  line `(d) record in writing, for the consideration of any such board or committee, any observations he`
  line `may think proper in regard to the proceedings or duties of the board or committee.`
  line
  line `(2) If any difference of opinion arises between officers exercising the powers conferred by`
  line `sub-section (1), it shall be referred--`
  line
  line `(a) if it arises between two or more Deputy Commissioners in the same divisionto the`
  line `Commissioner ; and`
  line
  line `(b) if it arises between two or more Deputy Commissioners in different divisions or between two`
  line `or more Commissionersto the Local Government;`
  line
  line `and the decision thereon of the Commissioner or of the Local Government, as the case may be, shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (43182)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to suspend action.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43182&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner of the division or the Deputy Commissioner of`
  line `the district may, by order in writing, suspend, within the division or district respectively, the execution of`
  line `any resolution or order of a district board or local board or joint committee, or prohibit the doing of any`
  line `act within the said limits which is about to be done, or is being done, in pursuance of or under cover of`
  line `this Act, if, in his opinion, the resolution, order or act is in. excess of the powers conferred by law, or the`
  line `execution of the resolution or order, or the doing of the act, is likely to lead to a breach of the peace, or to`
  line `cause injury or annoyance to the public or to any class or body or persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (43183)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Extraordinary powers of Deputy Commissioner in ease of emergency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43183&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) In cases of`
  line `emergency, the Deputy Commissioner may provide for the execution of any work, or the doing of any`
  line `act, which a district board or local board is empowered to execute or do, and the immediate execution or`
  line `doing of which is, in his opinion, necessary for the service or safety of the public, and may direct that the`
  line `expense of executing the work or of doing the act shall be forthwith paid by the district board.`
  line
  line `(2) if the expense is not so paid, the Deputy Commissioner may make an order directing the person`
  line `having the custody of the balance of the district fund to pay the expense, or so much thereof as is, from`
  line `time to time, possible, from that balance in priority to all other charges against the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (43184)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to provide for performance of duties in case of default of board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43184&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the`
  line `Commissioner, after due enquiry, is satisfied that a district board has made default in performing any duty`
  line `imposed upon it by or under this Act, he may, by an order in writing, fix a period for the performance of`
  line `that duty, and, if it is not performed within the period so fixed, he may appoint some person to perform it,`
  line `and may direct that the expense of performing it shall be paid, within such time as he may fix, by the`
  line `board to that person.`
  line
  line `(2) If the expense is not so paid, the Commissioner may make an order directing the person having`
  line `the custody of the balance of the district fund to pay the expense, or so much thereof as is, from time to`
  line `time, possible, from that balance in priority to all other charges against the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (43185)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to invest other officers with power of control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43185&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `When the control and administration of any public work is`
  line `by or under this Act transferred to a district board, and at the time of the transfer the cost of that control`
  line `and administration is defrayed from provincial revenue, the Local Government may invest any officer`
  line `with respect to that work with the powers of a Commissioner under section 44 or section 47, or with the`
  line `powers of a Deputy Commissioner under section 46.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (43186)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Report of action under preceding sections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43186&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `When the Commissioner makes any order under`
  line `section 45 or section 47, he shall forthwith forward to the Local Government, and when the Deputy Commissioner makes any order under section 45 or section 46, or an officer empowered under section 48`
  line `makes any order under section 46 or section 47, he shall forthwith forward to the Commissioner, for`
  line `submission to the Local Government, a copy of the order, with a statement of the reasons for making it,`
  line `and with such explanation, if any, as the board or committee concerned may wish to offer. The Local`
  line `Government may thereupon confirm, modify or rescind the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (43187)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Powers of Local Government and its officers over boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43187&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the`
  line `Local Government and of all Commissioners and Deputy Commissioners acting under its orders to`
  line `require that the proceedings of district boards and local boards shall be in conformity with law and with`
  line `the rules in force thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Local Government may exercise all powers necessary for the purpose of sub-section (1), and`
  line `may, amongst other things, by order in writing, annul any proceeding which it considers not to be in`
  line `conformity with law and with the said rules.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner of the division and the Deputy Commissioner of the district may, within their`
  line `jurisdiction, for the same purpose, exercise such .powers as may be conferred upon them by rules made in`
  line `this behalf by the Local Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (43753)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power of Local Government to supersede in case of incompetency, persistent default abuse of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. The words "with the previous approval of the Governor General in Council" omitted by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43753&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `If a district board or local board is not competent to perform, or persistently makes`
  line `default in the performance of, the duties imposed on it by or under this or any other Act, or exceeds or`
  line `abuses its powers, the Local Government may, ^1*** in Council, by notification, in which the reasons for`
  line `so doing shall be stated, declare the board to be superseded:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in case of public emergency, the notification may be issued without the previous`
  line `approval of the Governor General in Council, but shall be immediately reported to the Governor General`
  line `in Council and shall be subject to his orders.`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (43189)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Consequences of supersession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43189&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `When a district board or local board is superseded under`
  line `section 51, the following consequences shall ensue:--`
  line
  line `(a) All members of the board shall from the date of the notification vacate their offices as such`
  line `members:`
  line
  line `(b) All powers and duties of the board may, until the board is re-constituted, be exercised and.`
  line `performed by such person as the Local Government appoints in that behalf:`
  line
  line `(c) Where a district board is superseded, all property vested in it shall, until it is re-constituted,`
  line `vest in Tier Majesty.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (43190)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Constitution of new board, and transfer of functions of superseded local boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43190&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) When`
  line `a district board is superseded, Constitution the Local Government shall, as soon as in its judgment`
  line `conveniently may be, constitute another district board in its place.`
  line
  line `(2) When a local board is superseded, the Local Government may either constitute another local`
  line `board in its place, or transfer its functions to the district board or, by a notification under section 10, to`
  line `any other local board.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (43191)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title Disputes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43191&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `If any dispute, for the decision of which this Act does not otherwise provide, arises`
  line `between two or more boards constituted under this Act, or between a municipal committee or cantonment`
  line `authority and any such board, the matter shall be referred--`
  line
  line `(a) to the Deputy Commissioner, if the local authorities concerned are in the same district;`
  line
  line `(b) to the Commissioner or Commissioners of the division or divisions, if the local authorities`
  line `concerned are in different districts ; and`
  line
  line `(c) to the Local Government, if the local authorities concerned are in different divisions and the`
  line `Commissioners of those divisions cannot agree.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the authority to which any dispute is referred under this section shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) If, in the case mentioned in clause (a), the Deputy Commissioner is a member of one of the boards`
  line `or committees concerned, his functions under this section shall be discharged by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) "Local authority" in this section means a district board, local board, municipal committee or`
  line `cantonment authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (43192)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power of the Governor General in Council and the Local Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43192&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `So far`
  line `as may be consistent with the provisions of this Act--`
  line
  line `(1) the Governor General in Council may--`
  line
  line `(a) make general rules or special orders for the regulation of taxation under section 30; and`
  line
  line `^1[(b) regulation the powers of district boards to make vary and dispose of investments;]`
  line
  line `(2) the Local Government may, for any district or local board, or any class of such boards, make`
  line `rules for ^2[Rules made under clause (2)(b) shall be subject to the control of the Governor General in`
  line Council]--
  line
  line `(c) dividing boards into classes, and fixing the powers of boards of each class ;`
  line
  line `(d) determining the mode and time of appointment or election of members of boards, the term`
  line `of office, allowances (if any), and the qualifications and disqualifications of such members, and`
  line `the qualifications and disqualifications of voters, and generally for regulating all elections under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) regulating the. powers of boards to transfer property;`
  line
  line `(f) regulating the powers of boards to contract and do other things necessary for the purposes`
  line `of their constitution and the mode of executing contracts;`
  line
  line `(g) determining the intermediate offices, if any, through which correspondence between`
  line `boards or members of boards and the Local Government or its officers shall pass;`
  line
  line `(h) determining the language in which business shall be transacted;`
  line
  line `(i) the employment, payment, suspension and removal of officers and servants under`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `(j) the apportionment of the district fund between the general purposes of the district and. the`
  line `purposes of particular parts of the district;`
  line
  line `(k) the application of district funds;`
  line
  line `(l) the form of estimates of income and expenditure under section 39;`
  line
  line `(m) the form of accounts and. the manner of periodical audit under section 40;`
  line
  line `(n) the publication of abstracts of accounts under section 43;`
  line
  line `(o) the preparation of plans and estimates for works which are to be partly or wholly constructed at the expense of boards, and as to the authority by which, and the conditions Subject to`
  line `which, such plans and estimates may be sanctioned;`
  line
  line `(p) the powers of supervision to be exercised by Commissioners and Deputy Commissioners`
  line `under section 50 ;`
  line
  line `(q) the conduct of proceedings of boards, including the fixing of a quorum, the appointment`
  line `or election of a chairman, and the term of office of a chairman and vice-chairman;`
  line
  line `(r) the appointment and payment of auditors of the accounts of boards; and`
  line
  line `(s) the guidance of district boards when suits or other proceedings are intended to be or have`
  line `been instituted by or against them in Civil Courts; and`
  line
  line `(t) generally determining the relations between district boards and local boards, and guiding`
  line `boards and Government officers in all matters connected with the carrying out of the provisions`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `All such rules and alterations of rules shall be notified, and no rules or alteration of rules under clause (2)`
  line `(d) shall come into operation until three months-after-they have been notified ^3[Rules made under clause`
  line `(2)(b) shall be subject to the control of the Governor General in Council].`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. Added by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (43194)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43194&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every district board or local board empowered in. this behalf`
  line `by the Local Government may make regulations for carrying out all or any of the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A regulation made under this section shall not have effect until it has been confirmed by the Local`
  line `Government and published in such manner and for such time as the Local Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (43195)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Penalty for infringement of regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43195&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) In, making-any regulation under section 56, a`
  line `board may direct that a breach of the same shall be punished with fine which may extend to fifty rupees,`
  line `and, in the case of a continuing breach, with a further fine which may extend to five rupees for every day`
  line `during which the breach is continued after the offender has been convicted of such breach.`
  line
  line `(2) In default of payment of any fine imposed under this section, the defaulter shall be liable to simple`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to eight days:`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (43196)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title Prosecutions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43196&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Prosecutions under this Act for breach of regulations may be instituted by any`
  line `board, or by any person authorized by the board in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) A Judge or Magistrate shall not be deemed to be within the meaning of section 555 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure a party to, or personally interested in, any case under this section merely because he`
  line `is a member of the board.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (43198)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Liability of members of boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43198&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Every person shall be liable for the loss, waste Liability of or`
  line `misapplication of any money or other property members of belonging to the district board, if such loss,`
  line `waste or misapplication is a direct consequence of his neglect or misconduct while a member of a local`
  line `board or of the district board, and a suit for compensation for the same may be instituted against him in`
  line `such Court as the Local Government directs, by the district board with the sanction of the Commissioner,`
  line `or by the Secretary of State for India in Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (43199)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Procedure for making rules and regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43199&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government, before making`
  line `Procedure any rules under section 55 or section 67, and a district or local hoard, before making any`
  line `regulations rules and regulations, under section 56, shall publish, in such manner as the Local`
  line `Government may deem sufficient for giving information to persons interested, a draft of the proposed`
  line `rules or regulations, together with a notice specifying a date on or after which the draft will be taken into`
  line `consideration; and shall, before making the rules or regulations, receive and consider any objection or`
  line `suggestion which may be made by any person with respect to the draft before the date so specified.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such rule or regulation shall be published in the official Gazette in English and in such`
  line `other language as the Local Government directs, and such publication shall be conclusive evidence that`
  line `the rule or regulation has been made as required by this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (43200)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Acquisition of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43200&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Where any land is required for the purposes of this Act, the Local`
  line `Government may, at the request of a district board, proceed to acquire it under the provisions of the Land`
  line `Acquisition Act, 1870 (10 of 1870); and, on the payment by the board of the compensation awarded under`
  line `that Act, and of the charges incurred by the Government in connection with the proceedings, the land`
  line `shall vest in the board.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (43754)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Penalty on member, officer or servant being interested in contracts made with a board or joint committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43754&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any member, officer or servant of a district or local board or joint committee`
  line `appointed under this Act is, otherwise than with the permission in writing of the Commissioner, directly`
  line `or indirectly interested in any contract made with that board or joint committee, he shall be deemed to`
  line `have committed an offence under the Indian Penal Code, section 168.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not, by reason of being a shareholder in, or a member of, any incorporated or`
  line `registered company, be held to be interested, in any contract entered into between the company and a`
  line `board or committee; but he shall not take part in any proceedings of the board or committee relating to`
  line `any such contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (43202)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Saving for Act XI of 1879.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43202&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect the Local Authorities Loans`
  line `Act, 1879 (11 of 1879).`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (43203)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `General powers of Local Government and Commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43203&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `In all matters connected with this`
  line `Act, the Local Government shall have and exercise over Commissioners and Deputy Commissioners, and`
  line `Commissioners shall have and exercise over Deputy Commissioners,, the same authority and control as`
  line `they respectively have and. exercise over them in the general and revenue administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (43204)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Contracts of local Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43204&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Every contract entered into, whether in its own name or in the`
  line `name of the Government, by the, committee appointed in a district under section 11 of the Panjab. Local`
  line `Rates Act, 1878, may be enforced by and against the district board constituted for that district under this`
  line `Act, in like manner as it might have been by and against the committee if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (43205)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Government officers serving under committees to continue under board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43205&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `A Government`
  line `officer employed under the committee appointed in a district as aforesaid at the time when a district board`
  line `comes into existence for the district under section 17 of this Act shall be deemed to be similarly employed`
  line `by the board, and shall not be dismissed from that employment without the sanction of the Local`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (43206)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Power of Local Government to except local area from operation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43206&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `circumstances of any district or part of a district are, in the opinion of the Local Government, such that all`
  line `or any of the provisions of this chapter are unsuited thereto, the Local Government may, by notification in`
  line `the official Gazette, except the district or part from the operation of those provisions; and thereupon those`
  line `provisions shall not apply to the excepted district or part until again applied thereto by a like notification.`
  line
  line `(2) While any notification under this section is in force, the Local Government may make rules to`
  line `provide for any matter dealt with by the provisions to which the notification applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (43207)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Committee to be constituted for district wholly excepted from Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43207&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `When a district is`
  line `excepted, under section 67, from all the provisions of this chapter, a committee shall, except where the`
  line `Local Government for special reasons otherwise directs, be constituted for the control and administration`
  line `in that district of the matters mentioned in section 20, or of such of them as the Local Government may,`
  line `from time to time, specify; and the Local Government shall, from time to time, determine the manner in`
  line `which the members of the committee shall be appointed and removed, define the functions and authority`
  line `of the committee, and place at its disposal, subject to such control as the Local Government thinks fit,--`
  line
  line `(a) the balance standing at the credit of the district fund at the time when the district is excepted`
  line `or, as the case may be, the balance of the allotments made for the district under section 7 of the`
  line `Panjab Local Rates Act, 1878 (5 of 1878), and of the road and school cesses, which may be available`
  line `for expenditure in the district at that time;`
  line
  line `(b) all proceeds of rates which, but for the district being excepted, would be allotted to the district`
  line `board under section 9 of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other sources of income mentioned in section 35 of this Act as the Local Government`
  line `thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that not less than one-half of the members of the committee shall be persons who own`
  line `landed property or reside or carry on trade or business in the district and are not servants of the`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (43208)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to direct that Act XX of 1856 shall cease to be in force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43208&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any local area in`
  line `which Act 20 of 1856 (An Act to make better provision for the appointment and maintenance of Police`
  line `Chaukidars in Cities, Towns, Stations, Suburbs and Bazars in the Presidency of Fort William in Bengal)`
  line `is in force is included in any local area over which a district board established under this Act has`
  line `authority, the Local Government may, by notification, direct that that Act shall cease to be in force in the`
  line `local area BO included, and that every panchayat constituted under that Act for that local area shall cease`
  line `to exist.`
  line
  line `(2) When a direction is issued under this section in respect of any local area in. which the said Act 20`
  line `of 1856 is in force, the amount, if any, then available under section 36 of that Act for purposes of`
  line `improvement in that local area shall be expended therein by the Deputy Commissioner for such purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (43209)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Recovery of rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43209&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `All rates and taxes imposed under this Act, and all arrears of such rates and`
  line `taxes, may be recovered as if they were arrears of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (43210)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Local rate or tax how to be assessed and collected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43210&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may, by`
  line `notification, determine the persons by whom the local rate or any tax imposed under this Act shall be`
  line `assessed and collected, and make rules for the assessment and collection of the rate or tax, and direct in`
  line `what manner persons employed in the assessment or collection shall be remunerated.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of section 60 shall apply to all rules made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (43211)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43211&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) In matters connected with the assessment and collection of any rate or tax leviable`
  line `under this Act, an appeal shall lie from the order of any person authorized under this Act to make`
  line `assessments or collections to such person as the Local Government appoints:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appeal shall be presented within 30 days from the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The order passed on an appeal under this section shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (43212)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Instalments of rates and taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43212&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may, by notification, prescribe by`
  line `what instalments and at what times any rate or tax leviable under this Act shall be, payable:`
  line
  line `Provided that every instalment of the local rate leviable under section 5 shall be payable with an`
  line `instalment of the land-revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) In any local area subject to the authority of a district board the Local Government may, by`
  line `notification, delegate to the board, subject to such conditions as ifs thinks fit, its powers under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (43213)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Power of Local Government to exempt from taxation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43213&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The Local Government may, by`
  line `notification, remit or reduce any rate or tax imposed under this Act, or exempt any person or class of`
  line `persons, or any description of property, wholly or in any part, from liability to any such rate or tax, and`
  line `cancel any such remission, reduction or exemption.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (43214)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Power to direct measurements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43214&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `When measurements are necessary for the assessment of the`
  line `local rate or of any tax imposed under this Act, the Local Government may, by notification, direct such`
  line `measurements to be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (43755)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Suits relating to rates and taxes under this Act cognizable by Courts having cognizance of suits for rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43755&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `Suits for the recovery from co-sharers, tenants or others of any sum on account of any`
  line `rate or tax imposed under this Act, and suits on account of illegal exaction of any such rate or tax, or for`
  line `settlement of accounts connected therewith, shall, unless the Local Government otherwise directs, be`
  line `cognizable by the Courts which for the time being have cognizance of suits for rent due on land.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (43216)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Confirmation and recovery of existing rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780&sectionId=43216&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_188320_1523272812780
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `All rates for the maintenance of roads, schools`
  line `or the district-post, for the payment of which provision has been made in any settlement-record previous`
  line `to the passing of this Act, or which have been habitually levied by Government, shall be deemed to have`
  line `been and to be legally imposed, and to have been and to be legally recoverable as if they were arrears of`
  line `land-revenue payable directly to Government and due on the land in respect of which they are payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (43217)
